Program: Discovery
Title: Strange Senses
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry56
Last Broadcast Date: 16 July 2002
A report on the theory that animals can sense the Earth's magnetic field. Scientists are researching how so many animals, including birds and fish, are able to navigate their journeys by being able to detect the earth's magnetic field. Without these sense many animals would not be able to survive.